<div class="policy-page">
    <div class="hero-section">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last Updated: February 2, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-container">
        <div class="policy-content">
            <div class="intro-section">
                <p class="intro-text">
                    At PiggyPro, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
                    use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our personal budget management
                    application. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your
                    personal data.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Information We Collect -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

                <h3>1.1 Personal Information You Provide</h3>
                <p>When you register for PiggyPro, we collect the following information:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Username, email address, password (encrypted), first name, last name, and phone number (optional)</li>
                    <li><strong>Financial Data:</strong> Income amounts, expense transactions, budget allocations, savings goals, and category preferences</li>
                    <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> Any additional information you choose to add to your profile</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>1.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
                <p>When you use PiggyPro, we automatically collect certain information:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, time spent on the application, and interaction patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, operating system, IP address, and device identifiers</li>
                    <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> Error logs, access times, and system events for troubleshooting purposes</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>1.3 Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Important:</strong> PiggyPro does NOT collect or store:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Bank account credentials or login information</li>
                        <li>Credit card or payment information (the service is free)</li>
                        <li>Social Security Numbers or government-issued ID numbers</li>
                        <li>Biometric data</li>
                        <li>Location tracking data</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- How We Use Your Information -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>

                <div class="use-case">
                    <h4>2.1 To Provide and Maintain Our Service</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Create and manage your account</li>
                        <li>Process and store your financial transactions</li>
                        <li>Calculate budget allocations and track spending</li>
                        <li>Generate financial reports and analytics</li>
                        <li>Send notifications about budget alerts and goal achievements</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="use-case">
                    <h4>2.2 To Improve Our Service</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Analyze usage patterns to enhance user experience</li>
                        <li>Identify and fix technical issues</li>
                        <li>Develop new features based on user needs</li>
                        <li>Optimize application performance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="use-case">
                    <h4>2.3 To Communicate With You</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Send account verification emails</li>
                        <li>Provide customer support</li>
                        <li>Send important service updates or changes</li>
                        <li>Respond to your inquiries and requests</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="use-case">
                    <h4>2.4 To Ensure Security</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Detect and prevent fraud or unauthorized access</li>
                        <li>Monitor for security threats</li>
                        <li>Enforce our Terms of Service</li>
                        <li>Protect against malicious activities</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- How We Share Your Information -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>

                <div class="privacy-commitment">
                    <h3>Our Commitment: We Do NOT Sell Your Data</h3>
                    <p>
                        <strong>
                            PiggyPro will NEVER sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties
                            for marketing purposes.
                        </strong> Your financial data is private and belongs to you alone.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h3>Limited Data Sharing</h3>
                <p>We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>

                <div class="sharing-case">
                    <h4>3.1 With Your Consent</h4>
                    <p>We will share information when you explicitly authorize us to do so.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="sharing-case">
                    <h4>3.2 Service Providers</h4>
                    <p>We may share data with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our application:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Cloud hosting providers (for secure data storage)</li>
                        <li>Email service providers (for account verification and notifications)</li>
                        <li>Analytics providers (for application improvement)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Note:</strong> All service providers are contractually obligated to protect your data
                        and use it only for specified purposes.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="sharing-case">
                    <h4>3.3 Legal Requirements</h4>
                    <p>We may disclose information if required by law, such as:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Complying with legal processes (subpoenas, court orders)</li>
                        <li>Protecting our rights and property</li>
                        <li>Investigating potential violations of our Terms of Service</li>
                        <li>Protecting the safety of our users or the public</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="sharing-case">
                    <h4>3.4 Business Transfers</h4>
                    <p>
                        In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be
                        transferred. We will notify you before your data is transferred and becomes subject to
                        a different privacy policy.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Data Security -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information:</p>

                <div class="security-measure">
                    <h4>4.1 Encryption</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Data in Transit:</strong> All data transmitted between your device and our
                            servers is encrypted using SSL/TLS protocols
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Password Security:</strong> Passwords are hashed using PBKDF2 algorithm
                            before storage
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Data at Rest:</strong> Sensitive data is encrypted in our database</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="security-measure">
                    <h4>4.2 Access Controls</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Role-based access control (RBAC) for administrative functions</li>
                        <li>Multi-factor authentication available for user accounts</li>
                        <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
                        <li>Limited employee access to user data</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="security-measure">
                    <h4>4.3 Infrastructure Security</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Secure cloud hosting with regular backups</li>
                        <li>Firewall protection and intrusion detection systems</li>
                        <li>Regular software updates and security patches</li>
                        <li>Monitoring for suspicious activities</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Important:</strong> While we implement robust security measures, no system is
                        100% secure. Please use a strong, unique password and enable two-factor authentication
                        for additional protection.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Your Rights and Choices -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>5. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
                <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.1 Access and Update</h4>
                    <p>
                        You can access and update your account information at any time through the Profile
                        Settings page. You have the right to review all data we hold about you.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.2 Data Export</h4>
                    <p>
                        You can export your transaction data in CSV format from the Reports page. We will
                        provide a complete copy of your data upon request.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.3 Account Deletion</h4>
                    <p>
                        You may request deletion of your account and all associated data by contacting us at
                        <a href="mailto:support@piggypro.com">support@piggypro.com</a>. We will delete your data
                        within 30 days of verification.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.4 Notification Preferences</h4>
                    <p>
                        You can manage email notification preferences in your Profile Settings. You may opt
                        out of non-essential communications while still receiving critical account notifications.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.5 Data Portability</h4>
                    <p>
                        Upon request, we will provide your data in a structured, commonly used format that
                        allows you to transfer it to another service.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-item">
                    <h4>5.6 Opt-Out Rights</h4>
                    <p>You have the right to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Opt out of marketing communications</li>
                        <li>Disable cookies (though this may affect functionality)</li>
                        <li>Request restriction of processing in certain circumstances</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Data Retention -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                    We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide our services and comply
                    with legal obligations:
                </p>

                <div class="retention-policy">
                    <h4>6.1 Active Accounts</h4>
                    <p>While your account is active, we retain all your data to provide continuous service.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="retention-policy">
                    <h4>6.2 Inactive Accounts</h4>
                    <p>
                        If you do not log in for 24 months, we will send an email notification. After 30 months
                        of inactivity, we may delete your account and data unless you reactivate it.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="retention-policy">
                    <h4>6.3 Deleted Accounts</h4>
                    <p>
                        Upon account deletion request, we will delete all personal data within 30 days.
                        However, we may retain certain information for:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Legal compliance (tax records, audit trails)</li>
                        <li>Fraud prevention</li>
                        <li>Resolving disputes</li>
                        <li>Enforcing our Terms of Service</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Such data is anonymized where possible and deleted after legal retention periods expire.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="retention-policy">
                    <h4>6.4 Backup Retention</h4>
                    <p>
                        Backup copies may persist in our systems for up to 90 days after deletion but are
                        not accessible or used for any purpose.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Children's Privacy -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
                <div class="age-restriction">
                    <p><strong>PiggyPro is not intended for children under 18 years of age.</strong></p>
                    <p>
                        We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18. If you are
                        a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information,
                        please contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:support@piggypro.com">support@piggypro.com</a>.
                        We will delete such information from our systems.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- International Users -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>8. International Users</h2>
                <p>PiggyPro is operated in Singapore. If you access our service from outside Singapore:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your information may be transferred to and processed in Singapore</li>
                    <li>By using PiggyPro, you consent to the transfer of your information to Singapore</li>
                    <li>
                        We will take appropriate safeguards to ensure your data is protected in accordance
                        with this Privacy Policy
                    </li>
                    <li>We comply with applicable data protection laws, including GDPR for EU users</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- Third-Party Links -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
                <p>
                    PiggyPro may contain links to third-party websites or services (e.g., tutorials, resources).
                    This Privacy Policy does not apply to those external sites. We are not responsible for the
                    privacy practices of third parties. We encourage you to read their privacy policies before
                    providing any information.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Cookies and Tracking -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>10. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>

                <h3>10.1 What Are Cookies?</h3>
                <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device that help us provide and improve our service.</p>

                <h3>10.2 Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <h4>Essential Cookies</h4>
                    <p>
                        Required for the application to function. These include session cookies that maintain
                        your login state.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <h4>Functional Cookies</h4>
                    <p>Remember your preferences and settings (e.g., notification preferences).</p>
                </div>

                <div class="cookie-type">
                    <h4>Analytics Cookies</h4>
                    <p>Help us understand how users interact with PiggyPro to improve the service.</p>
                </div>

                <h3>10.3 Managing Cookies</h3>
                <p>
                    You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling cookies may
                    affect the functionality of PiggyPro, particularly login and session management.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Changes to Privacy Policy -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>We will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page</li>
                    <li>For material changes, we will send an email notification to registered users</li>
                    <li>We will display a prominent notice within the application</li>
                    <li>Your continued use of PiggyPro after changes constitutes acceptance of the new policy</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Contact Information -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data
                    practices, please contact us:
                </p>

                <div class="contact-info">
                    <div class="contact-method">
                        <strong>Email:</strong>
                        <p><a href="mailto:support@piggypro.com">support@piggypro.com</a></p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="contact-method">
                        <strong>Contact Form:</strong>
                        <p><a href="/contact">Submit an inquiry through our contact page</a></p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="contact-method">
                        <strong>Response Time:</strong>
                        <p>We will respond to all inquiries within 7 business days</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="contact-method">
                        <strong>Mailing Address:</strong>
                        <p>
                            PiggyPro Team<br>
                            Singapore Polytechnic<br>
                            School of Computing<br>
                            500 Dover Road<br>
                            Singapore 139651
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Legal Compliance -->
            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>13. Legal Compliance</h2>
                <p>PiggyPro complies with applicable data protection laws, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA)</strong> - Singapore</li>
                    <li><strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong> - European Union</li>
                    <li><strong>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</strong> - United States</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    If you are a resident of the EU, California, or other jurisdictions with specific data
                    protection rights, please contact us for information about exercising those rights.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Your Consent -->
            <div class="consent-section">
                <h2>Your Consent</h2>
                <p>
                    By using PiggyPro, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy
                    and agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein.
                </p>
                <p>If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please discontinue use of PiggyPro immediately.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Quick Links -->
            <div class="quick-links-section">
                <h3>Related Documents</h3>
                <div class="links-grid">
                    <a href="/terms" class="policy-link">Terms of Service</a>
